.TH clear 3
.SH NAME
\*Lclear\*O, \*Lwclear\*O \- Clears a window
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint clear(\|)\*O

\*Lint wclear(\*Vwin\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "clear macro"
.iX "wclear subroutine"
The \*Lclear\*O routine resets the entire default
window to blanks and sets the current
(y, x) coordinates to (0, 0).
.PP
The routine \*Lwclear\*O resets the entire specified
window to blanks and sets the current
(y, x) coordinates to (0, 0).
.PP
The \*Lclear\*O routine assumes that the screen may have
stray characters on it that it does not know about.
The routine first calls \*Lerase\*O
which copies blanks to every position in the default window,
and then \*Lclearok\*O,
which clears the physical screen completely on the next call to
\*Lrefresh\*O for \*Lstdscr\*O.
.PP
The routine \*Lclear\*O is a macro.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lclear\*O and \*Lwclear\*O
functions return OK on success and ERR on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Lclearok\*O(3), \*Lerase\*O(3), \*Lrefresh\*O(3)
.EQ
